Whatever Canadaâs historic ties to Britain, the symbolism of a hereditary monarch is antithetical to a modern democracy that aspires to meritocratic advancement and guarantees equality before the law. Politically, Canadians would never accept the actual exercise of the powers of our head of state by the King or Queen of Britain. We are no longer a British colony and the law must evolve to reflect this change.
